Happy 2023! And YES, let’s make it the year we really make our dreams come true. 

Let’s create time for more joy. More fun. More laughter. 

Let’s dream bigger and feel inspired and lit up by being here in the now. 

Let’s fill our hearts, nourish our souls, and bring ideas and visions to life. 

Starting 2023 with a full moon ritual, setting new year intentions, saying affirmations, journaling what I want to manifest this year. 

For most of 2022, I met with my mentor @sarahcentrella and an intimate group of coaches every Monday at 5:30pm on Zoom.

We went through the first 12 weeks of lesson modules to get to the root of our money and self worth blocks, finding out if we’re a dreamer or a thinker (I’m a DREAMER!) 🌼

We dove deep into our personal work to know what truly makes us happy and wrote down dreams #bucketlist style full of #livelist experiences we want to call into our lives. 

We made vision boards that are wayyyy beyond the usual random pins of aesthetic photos posted on Pinterest boards to pop them up on the wall and cross fingers it *might* happen. Nope. We did it way better.

When we made our Futureboards, we knew exactly what our future vision would look like to manifest our dreams into reality. We made our #LifePlan VISION.

We said our affirmations out loud in the shower, in the car, daily. And it works. 

Only a few months after my Futureboard was up on my wall, things started to happen.

It’s powerful. 

And I’m SO EXCITED to share I am now a certified Centrella Method coach. 

My *new* website is: stephanie-dianne (dot) com 

Are you ready to manifest your dream life you really want to live? 

Let’s chat 1:1 face to face together. DM me!

I’m opening the magic doors to Transformation Bootcamp this January 2023. 

Curious? Book a strategy call via my Calendly (link in bio).

It’s the best thing I did for myself last year, and I’m offering transformation coaching to you, this year, this month, this week, this day!

Today is the day. Never too late to start, so let’s connect! 

xo Stephanie

story about a girl (poem)

I’m still the girl I was 
who’s eyes lit up eating strawberries
same girl who dipped them
in whipped cream
she wanted strawberries on her birthday cake
she popped maraschino cherries into her mouth 
also buttered corn in summer
pad thai noodles, bean and cheese burritos

she pretended to be Princess Leia, twisted her long brown hair into cinnamon buns 

she loved roller skating to disco
boogie boarding the waves

she drew unicorns
wore a rainbow tube top
white and purple Dolphin shorts, Cherokee wedge sandals

That girl in glasses
She felt like the tallest girl in school, the girl who wanted to play cello, instead, string bass in orchestra 

she wished for a pink bicycle with a banana seat

she wished upon a star
to become
the woman she is 

the girl who read encyclopedias and loved ancient Roman myths 
the girl who practiced Beethoven on the piano 

the girl who loved running through the sprinklers
doing cartwheels in the grass

the girl who listened to the Beatles on the record player while eating too many apple Jolly Ranchers

the girl who wanted to become the woman I am
she is still that girl

“Tell me, what is it you plan to do with your one wild and precious life?” (Mary Oliver)

🎉Celebrating how far I’ve come. 

Do you ever look back on your life and realize how good your life has become? And it’s just getting better. 

Ten years ago, l was a struggling single mom of three who slept in the living room of a tiny (and expensive!) apartment so the kids could have their own rooms. I was so burnt out yet had to keep going. 

I didn’t see the blessings in my life because I was complaining about everything and focused on all of my problems. 

Ten years later, I’m flourishing, finding my purpose, and calling in all that I desire. Now I’m a home owner, paying less per month on my mortgage than that tiny expensive apartment. 

I’m grateful. I’m blessed. I’m completely in alignment with my higher power. Totally tuned into the universe on high frequency! ✨

It feels freaking awesome when I wake up each day full of energy and excitement!

I’m in great health. I get good sleep. I’m feeling good with daily exercise and healthy food. I’m making new friends and nurturing long-standing friendships. 

My coaching business is only beginning. I know I have the ability to guide other women who are feeling stuck and frustrated in their lives. 

I know I can inspire you! 

📣Message me if you’re interested in having a chat about how to make positive changes. 

We aren’t here to live a mediocre life. We are here to be magnificent. We are here to radiate and love and enjoy life.

xo, Stephanie

↺ Back in 2011: I was totally burnt out, depleted and exhausted, trying to get back into pre-pregnancy shape after my 3rd baby by following a strict raw vegan diet and taking spin, barre, and Pilates classes every damn day. I was also drinking a lot of wine to relax! 🍷

What I didn't know then was that my extreme behavior was causing more stress than anything else 😱

And then an early onset menopause just had to make an appearance! Hot flashes, night sweats, weight gain, uncontrollable crying -all of it became an unwelcome part of my life. 

I was suffering so much from stress and couldn’t take it anymore! What the heck?! I was only 41 years old. 

I just wanted to feel like myself again. 😭broke down sobbing in my doctor’s office after she told me I had to get my hormones in balance and reduce stress. 

(Yup, I left the doctor’s visit with a prescription for Xanax AND bio identical hormone creams.)

Gosh, I felt like such a hot mess! 

𝐍𝐎𝐖 ➜My lifestyle has shifted to self-care and a gentler approach to mind-body-spirit wellness.

Instead of “crushing it” in the gym, I’m intuitively doing whatever feels good. Yoga, walking, nature hikes, and free weights - all feel amazing!

What also works for me: eating plant-based🌿sleeping well, and little to no caffeine or alcohol.

Also, I took a deep dive into my health and got on some custom probiotics + supplements 🧡 feeling so amazing on my @viome supps now! 

I’m here to support women in midlife using the knowledge I’ve gained on my own mindset + wellness journey. 

Sharing a little about this because I'm creating a reset program for midlife women using everything I've learned ➜cultivating an abundance mindset, affirmations & meditations, plus plant-based recipes, weekly menus, and a gratitude journal ᯐall together in a 12 week course! 

I'm honestly super excited about this and cannot wait to share more!

xo, Stephanie

😅I went from burnt out exhausted single mom to feeling vibrant and truly living an abundant life 🎉

➤Back in my early 40s, my idea of a morning routine was to fuel up with a sugary scone and a tall chai soy latte at Starbucks while taking my three kids to school. I needed that caffeine and sugar rush to wake up! 

But my body and soul craved REAL nourishment. ❌not sugary scones
❌syrupy sweet lattes

I was caught up in the fast-paced hustle that wore me down with stress. 

Wanting to feel better and lose weight, I tried an extreme workout regimen and 💯 raw vegan diet, which only left me even more depleted. 

I struggled with:
🔥hot flashes
🔥night sweats
😵‍💫insomnia
🤕migraines

Yep, menopause showed up too early. 

I drank wine 🍷 to relax but it made me feel even more exhausted.

I was so stressed out it caused me to lose clumps of hair 😱OMG 

I gained weight though I exercised like crazy - which made me more fatigued from adrenal burnout. 

In an endless cycle of stress, anxiety, and exhaustion, I didn’t know what to do. 

The most painful part was feeling disconnected from my own feminine power. I was so stuck. 

Midlife ladies, can you relate?

Now: I wake up most mornings feeling refreshed 😌then🧘‍♀️meditate
journal📔drink tea 🍵 do 🧘‍♀️ yoga 
walk + go to the gym 💪🏻

I eat a healthy breakfast 🍏🫐🥑and feel nourished - supplements and lemon water 🍋 are my best friends! 

I've been sugar-free & plant-based vegan for years - totally works for me. 

It’s so good to feel energized!

Despite being in my early 50s, I feel much much younger. And according to recent blood test results, I'm biologically a whole decade younger.

I'm also less stressed now that my life has more feminine ease and flow.  

Sure, there are days when I feel off or a little blah, but I'm more balanced in mind, body, and spirit because I know I can reset. 

Have you faced any challenges like I have? What hasn't worked for you? What would you change?

Drop your comments below 👇🏻 
XO Steph

Have you ever had one of those days where it just seems like the universe isn’t your magical Amazon drone fairy delivering just what you ordered?

You asked universe for “more abundance” and you sure got it: 
➜an abundance of dirty dishes in the sink
➜an abundance of unexpected expenses
➜an abundance of weeds in your yard

Why? Because that’s what your thoughts and words were putting out into the universe. 

Well, there's a better way to ask for the abundance you want to manifest. 

CHOOSE YOUR THOUGHTS.

The way you think and how you focus on thoughts and how you say words out loud act as keywords in the universe's algorithm. 

That's right! Every intentional thought and emotion has potential to attract its energetic match into your life. 

Keep in mind that even the simplest shift in your perspective can create profound change if rooted in INTENTIONAL thought.

❌What not to do:
If you said out loud, “I don’t want electricity in my bedroom anymore” because you want to sleep without WiFi and EMF and Bluetooth, be careful what you say.

The keywords you just put into the universe’s algorithm was “no electricity” aand… 

🙊You may have sent out the intentional thought of “no electricity” to the universe. 

⚠️Be clear with your thoughts and intentions!

I said “I don’t want electricity!” out loud — I wanted to make my bedroom an electricity free zone. And guess what?

😱The very next day I got a call from my electric company — the power was scheduled to be turned off because the bill was overdue - since I didn’t check to see if it was on autopay, duh. 🙈🙈🙈

Do you see how powerful your words are? 

✅What to do: 
➤Focus your thoughts and intentions on what you want.
➤Get clear and state it out loud. This is how manifesting with affirmations actually work!
➤Feel as if it is already true. When feeling and emotion is matched with what you want it is on its way to already being your current experience.

That’s when manifestation happens. 

Thoughts ➜ words ➜ manifestation!

#manifestationtips #stephaniedianne #manifestinghacks #yourwordsmatter 
#universequotes

Hey, can we talk about perfection for a minute?

I got a message from a Facebook friend who refused to “like” my coaching page because she "really cannot emotionally cope with all that perfection." 

Perfection? I felt my stomach twist into a knot. 

She doesn't know how many times I felt less than perfect.

I’m not here to flaunt so-called perfection. I’m here to empower women to be their most radiant.

But gosh, that inbox message really triggered a soft spot in me.

The woman who told me I was "too perfect" doesn't know I used to worry about what others thought of me.

A shy awkward girl, I hid in the school library at lunch. I was tall, wore glasses and braces, and painfully insecure. 

A clique of mean girls in middle school - no joke, two were named Heather - told the whole class to RSVP to my 14th birthday party... and not show up.

Ghosted by my entire class on my birthday, I sat alone with birthday balloons, cake, and Purple Rain blasting on the stereo.

No one came to my 14th birthday party, thanks to the Heathers. 

I was so upset, I promised myself I’d never be rejected... and went into people pleasing mode. 

People pleasing made me choose abusive boyfriends, fake friends, and toxic situations.

My desire to be "perfect" made me feel “not good enough.”

Afraid to be “too much” I made myself “less than.”

➜I was told... by an envious aunt I was... too beautiful. So I tried to dim my beauty.

➜I was told... by a modeling agent I needed to lose 15 lbs because my legs were “chunky Kentucky Fried Chicken legs.” So I tried to lose weight. 

➜I was told... by a man I liked I was “too much." So I tried to be less so he might love me. 

➜I was told... by my adoptive mother I was a worthless b-word.  So I allowed her abuse.

➜I was told... by an employer I was a "throwaway child" and I’d never be "good enough" at anything. So I believed her instead of myself.

Then one day I said… F that! 

Now I choose me over others’ opinions, even if they think I'm too perfect. 

Not until my 40s did I realize people's opinions of me don't determine who I am or what I can achieve. 

Now I’m being the best version of myself… unapologetically. 

❤️ Steph

It’s giving eat the rainbow vibes 🌈🥑🥬🍠

As a woman of many talents, interests, passions, I love to share all that I’m into. 

Yet, I overthink what to share on each social media account before I actually post. 

I’ve deleted so many posts after editing, writing a caption, posting. 

B/c it’s all a bit overwhelming. Instagram, Facebook, Threads, TikTok. *puts phone down* wanna put my feet in grass, feel sun on my face, read a book. 

When I was a kid, we had Atari. 13 tv channels. A dial phone attached to the wall. 

We also had pinball, Pac-Man, Centipede, Galaga— in which I kicked major butt, lasered down all the invaders, and def needed more quarters for. 

I am (in essence) an introverted creative-artist-writer-cook-mama who just loves the act of creating. 

It occurs to me that it doesn’t have to be that deep. 

Can’t I be one of those people who just posts random selfies without edits? 

As a multi-creative, I’m often just figuring out what part of myself to show up as - I don’t fit into a box. I’m messy and complex. 

That said, this beautiful food rainbow fits into a bowl so simply with its complexity and messy eating potential.

This SWEET POTATO BURRITO BOWL w/GOLDEN HEIRLOOM TOMATO SALSA caught my eye as I was looking for something to share on my other/vegan food account—@plantfullkitchen — as I am renewing it as an account where I SHARE recipes more than CREATE them— because I love to share what lights me up! 

This plant-based bowl is by Noha of @leeksnbeets who is so inspirational with her choice of flavors and colors. Noha’s new cookbook, The Vegan Middle Eastern Cookbook, is NOW AVAILABLE for pre-order, so go follow her and get a copy! 

AND PLEASE go follow Noha, and if you haven’t already followed @plantfullkitchen I’d love to see you there too (recipe in post).

🙏🏻Thank you to Noha @leeksnbeets for creating this gorgeous bowl.

How do you set an INTENTION?

#intention #setintentions #manifestingmagic #manifest #manifesting #manifestingmindset #mindsetmatters #lawofattractioncoach

There’s a key 🔑 to really understanding how our thoughts, words, and emotions magnetize what we desire to manifest.

Do you want to know what the magic keys🔑🗝️to manifesting are?

Six things you may not know about me:

🩷When I was about two years old, my favorite album was Sgt. Pepper’s Lonely Hearts Club Band. I kept the record player by my bedside and listened to it often. All through my childhood I was obsessed with The Beatles, and I tuned in whenever there was a weekend long "Beatles A to Z" radio broadcast. 

🎹I began classical piano at age six and loved to play Chopin and Beethoven. I also love jazz piano and met many jazz greats, like Herbie Hancock and Ellis Marsalis. 

🎨I attended the New York Academy of Art for fine art classes in 1983, the summer I turned 13. My family sorted out my enrollment by adding just a few years to my actual age. Fortunately, my artistic abilities in drawing and painting from live models were at the level to support the whole ruse that I was almost 17. I loved being in the atelier with a palette of oil paints and canvas every day. 

🍰I’m a trained chef — graduated from culinary school in French classic cooking and pastry. I loved creating tarts and cakes the most! My first attempt at baking genoise (sponge cake) was perfection. My second attempt at genoise was… total flat dry matzah. Now I enjoy using my culinary know-how to create healthy plant-based recipes. 

🚂After a breakup in my mid-20s, I took the Amtrak train around the country for over a month and a half — Los Angeles to Chicago, to D.C., stayed in Virginia, then onward down the East Coast to Florida, and (never ever again) a bus —a horrible, dreadful, connector bus— from the coast of Florida to the gulf (boarding at 3am no less), then boarded the train again, thankfully, through the panhandle to New Orleans, and back to Los Angeles.

🚙When I returned from my train adventure, I decided to leave Los Angeles and drove myself to New Orleans with just a Thomas Guide road map for directions. Yes, it’s just a straight drive on the Interstate 10 Highway from Los Angeles to Louisiana, but back then, there were no cell phones or GPS! It ended up being one of the best chapters of my life.

👉🏼Write about where you are right now. Be honest with yourself. It’s okay.

👉🏼Make a bucket list of life experiences (not goals) that you want to make happen. Dream big! 

👉🏼Start a morning routine. Get up a little earlier. Make tea. Journal. Go for a gratitude walk. Listen to affirmation audios or podcasts that inspire you. Set a daily intention. Focus on what you want to experience.

👉🏼Pay attention to what’s working. Keep focusing on what feels good. 

👉🏼Stop yourself when you complain or talk negatively. Replace those words/thoughts with an idea, a goal, a dream, a vision of what you desire in life.
